Magnus: Mouse Advanced GNU Speech
=================================

The organization of the source release of Magnus is as follows:

+ magnus/
  + build.xml
  + cfg/
  + ChangeLog
  + CHANGES
  + COPYING
  + CREDITS
  + HACKING
  + img/
  + INSTALL
  + lib/
  + README
  + scilabworks/
  + sphinx4-1.0beta/
  + src/

The tree above can be easily obtained with the "ls -l" command on a
Linux console. In alphabetical order, the elements listed above are
described in the following lines. Probably yet many unknown concepts 
are to be found, especially if this is the first time the reader
deals with the project. There's no worry to take care of since in
the Thesis every aspect is described in detail.

>> magnus/
This is the root directory of the project. As it can be seen in the
tree, all the rest of the elements are descendants of this parent
folder.

>> build.xml
This is an "ant" script file. "Ant" is a builder for Java projects.
It enables the whole project precompilation with an extremely simple
set of commands. For its usage instructions please refer to the
INSTALL file.

>> cfg/
This folder contains the configuration files needed by Magnus, which
indicate the elements required for the speech recognizer, as well as
the dictionary and grammar rules established for the program to
work correctly.

>> ChangeLog
This text file indicates all the changes applied to the project's
fileset.

>> CHANGES
This text file keeps a record of all the changes applied to the
project between releases.

>> COPYING
This file contains a copy of the license applied to Magnus, which
is the GPLv3.

>> CREDITS
This text file contains a reference to all the projects that Magnus
makes use of to run.

>> HACKING
This is the text file that the reader is reading at this moment.
It describes every file contained in the project root folder.

>> img/
This folder contains the images that are used by Magnus.

>> INSTALL
This text file describes the intall process, as well as the
commands to carry it out and run Magnus successfully.

>> lib/
This folder contains the necessary resources to run Magnus.

>> README
This text file gives a general description of Magnus.

>> scilabworks/
Speech enhancement experiments with Scilab.

>> sphinx4-1.0beta/
This folder contains Sphinx4, the free speech recognition
software on which Magnus is built.

>> src/
This folder keeps the Magnus source files. Apart from the
configuration files, installation scripts and a few
precise modifications applied to Sphinx4, in this folder
there should be encountered all the needed information
to run Magnus successfully or contribute to the project's
developement.
